						<div class="postbody">Nope, DPCM basically causes at least one extra $4016/$4017 read when it occurs at the critical moment. The external device would think your code did two normal reads, unless it ignored two reads very close together. That might be doable, given the external device would probably be doing communication in software anyway.</div>

