				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Yes. It also happens with CHR ROM readback in $2007. The clock pulses will be at least six CPU cycles apart for legit reads or generally two for spurious reads. It's possible to have legit reads four cycles apart (e.g. <strong>ldx $4700 lda $4700</strong>), but if it's too hard to tell legit reads from spurious reads in your code, you can specify that the program always execute some other instruction between reads from your adapter's port.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

