			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">So a solution might be something like this...
<br />
<br />1. NES reads byte from MCU
<br />2. Read triggers MCU interrupt.  MCU starts a timer, loads next output byte to a temp variable.
<br />3. Timer expiration causes a second MCU interrupt; MCU copies temp variable to output.
<br />
<br />If a second read occurs before the timer expires, it gets an empty value.  Instead of resetting the timer, it could increment a counter to track the number of dupe reads.  Wouldn't necessarily need that value, but it would be interesting to see how often it happens.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
						<tr valign="middle">
							<td class="gensmall" align="right">
							
